Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Gradually stir milk into Gravy Mix with whisk in medium saucepan. Stirring frequently, cook on medium heat until gravy comes to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Stir in cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard and ham. Spread mixture in glass pie plate sprayed with no stick cooking spray. Sprinkle with cheese. Top with pickle chips, if desired. Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with sliced baguette or crackers.